// Infestation - a BioMech swarm breeding out of control (a Cosmos approximation of the
// Artemis 2.x Infestation scenario; see infest.md for the 2.x reference). When the
// raiders thin out, BioMechs boil in; they evolve (biomech_a..d, the art carries the
// escalating stats) and, once a Stage 4 matures, breed litters of Stage 1. Exterminate
// them to win. Cosmos has no built-in BioMech AI, so the behavior is scripted in
// siege.mast's siege_boss_infestation hook (spawn/evolve/reproduce, bounded so it stays
// winnable). BioMechs are raider-roled, so clearing them wins via siege_won.

# [Infestation](infestation)
---
Trigger: enemies_low
Low: 40%
Hook: siege_boss_infestation
---
A BioMech swarm erupts across the sector - they breed faster than they can be culled.

## [Purge the Infestation](purge_infestation)
---
Scope: shared
State: active
Parent: siege_mission
Goal: destroy 10 biomechs
Pays: 700 credits
---
Cull the BioMech swarm - every hull you burn slows the breeding.
